Q1. Store raw data into hdfs location
Answer ->
 hdfs dfs -put /home/cloudera/hive_class/sales_data1.csv /hive_class/
 
_________________________________________________________________________

Q2. Create a internal hive table "sales_order_csv" which will store csv data sales_order_csv .. make sure to skip header row while creating table
Answer ->
create table sales_order_csv
(
ORDERNUMBER int,
QUANTITYORDERED int,
PRICEEACH float,
ORDERLINENUMBER int,
SALES float,
STATUS string,
QTR_ID int,
MONTH_ID int,
YEAR_ID int,
PRODUCTLINE string,
MSRP int,
PRODUCTCODE string,
PHONE string,
CITY string,
STATE string,
POSTALCODE string,
COUNTRY string,
TERRITORY string,
CONTACTLASTNAME string,
CONTACTFIRSTNAME string,
DEALSIZE string
)
row format delimited
fields terminated by ','
tblproperties("skip.header.line.count"="1");

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Q3. Load data from hdfs path into "sales_order_csv"
Answer ->
load data inpath '/hive_class/sales_data1.csv' into table sales_order_csv;

____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Q4. Create an internal hive table which will store data in ORC format "sales_order_orc"
Answer ->
create table sales_order_orc
(
ORDERNUMBER int,
QUANTITYORDERED int,
PRICEEACH float,
ORDERLINENUMBER int,
SALES float,
STATUS string,
QTR_ID int,
MONTH_ID int,
YEAR_ID int,
PRODUCTLINE string,
MSRP int,
PRODUCTCODE string,
PHONE string,
CITY string,
STATE string,
POSTALCODE string,
COUNTRY string,
TERRITORY string,
CONTACTLASTNAME string,
CONTACTFIRSTNAME string,
DEALSIZE string
)
stored as orc;
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Q5. Load data from "sales_order_csv" into "sales_order_orc"
Answer ->
from sales_order_csv insert overwrite table sales_order_orc select *;
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Q6. Calculate total sales per year
Answer ->
select sum(SALES),YEAR_ID from sales_order_orc group by YEAR_ID;

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Q7. Find a product for which maximum orders were placed
Answer ->
select sum(QUANTITYORDERED),PRODUCTLINE from sales_order_orc group by PRODUCTLINE;
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________



